{"cursor":"17243","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nA 'pattern' in sewing and fashion design is an original garment from which other\ngarments of a similar style are copied. It can also refer to the paper or\ncardboard templates from which the parts of a garment are traced onto fabric\nbefore cutting out and assembling (sometimes called 'paper patterns').\n\n'Patternmaking', 'pattern making' or 'pattern cutting' is the art of\ndesigning patterns.\n\nA custom-fitted basic pattern from which patterns for many different styles can\nbe created is called a 'sloper' or 'block'.\n","linknr":353,"url":"Pattern_(sewing)","recorded":1362671384,"links":30,"instances":["sewing","sewing","designer","sewing","sewing","sewing"],"pdf":["http://www.techexchange.com/library/Patternmaking%20-%20Past%20to%20Present.pdf"],"categories":["Sizes in clothing","Sewing","Sewing equipment","History of clothing (Western fashion)","History of fashion"],"headings":["Pattern making","Patterns for home sewing","Evolution of American sewing pattern manufacturers","Patterns for commercial clothing manufacture","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Pattern_tracing_in_a_sewing_class_crop.jpg/220px-Pattern_tracing_in_a_sewing_class_crop.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/Sewing_pattern.jpg/200px-Sewing_pattern.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Fitting_muslin_dummy.jpg/220px-Fitting_muslin_dummy.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d4/Vintage_sewing_pattern_pieces.jpg/80px-Vintage_sewing_pattern_pieces.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5d/Tracing_pattern_sewing.jpg/120px-Tracing_pattern_sewing.jpg","//upload.w